it was like a gigantic horse,'' dunne said. ``it's so fresh for new york. everyone is smiling and happy, even the cops were happy.''
four years after a big mining company decided to phase out its operations in copperhill, the village tucked in the appalachian mountains of southeast tennessee has filed for bankruptcy protection
i don't know where else to scratch,'' copperhill mayor sylvan green said in a telephone interview, calling tuesday's chapter 9 federal court filing a last resort for the town of about 400 people about 60 miles east of chattanooga
much of the problem for copperhill derives from a long-standing dispute over a sewer and water service deal with neighboring mccaysville, ga. the dispute began when tennessee chemical co. said it was bailing out
back in 1979, copperhill's mining operations were owned by cities service co., the town decided to buy extra water from mccaysville to supply what was easily polk county's largest employer
that prompted mccaysville to float a bond issue on a new water plant and agree to pay copperhill for sewer service
then in 1982, tennessee chemical co. bought the mining operations. two years later, it said it couldn't compete with cheap imported copper and announced plans to lay off 900 workers by 1987
suddenly, copperhill no longer needed extra water, and when it stopped paying for it, mccaysville began withholding its $3,000 monthly payments for sewer service. that was about two years ago
they were to purchase ... almost 50 percent of our water, depending upon the tennessee chemical company,'' said mccaysville mayor barbara thomas
of course, the tennessee chemical company did not come through with their part of the bargain,'' she said. ``but that was not the contract we had. we had the contract with copperhill.''
mccaysville claims copperhill owes $255,000 in back water payments. copperhill wants payment for sewer service. negotiations failed and lately, said mrs. thomas, they haven't even been able to agree on when to talk
the loss of the sewer payments put such a dent in copperhill's budget that green told officials last year that the city could not finish building its new police station
in the petition filed in u.s. bankruptcy court, copperhill listed debts to 12 creditors totaling $302,355.49
a chapter 9 bankruptcy is designed to allow a municipal government to maintain necessary levels of service while it implements a plan to adjust its debts
coastal residents were jolted awake by a moderate earthquake and aftershock today, prompting worried calls to police. there were no reports of injury or damage, officials said
the first shock, measuring 3.9 on the richter scale, hit at 12:42 a.m. and was centered 11 miles southeast of downtown, said robert finn, spokesman for the seismology lab at the california institute of technology in pasadena
fifteen minutes later, an aftershock measured 2.7 on the richter scale
the temblors were felt in nearby goleta and isla vista, and southward in carpinteria, ojai, ventura and oxnard, about 30 miles away, finn said
these quakes weren't strong enough to do much damage, but a lot of people felt them,'' finn said
about 30 people telephoned santa barbara county sheriff's headquarters after the earth movement to confirm what they felt, said deputy larry ralston
they were just concerned and curious, or like one who wanted to know if he had been dreaming,'' ralston said
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on seismographs. every increase of one number means a tenfold increase in magnitude
an earthquake of 3.5 on the richter scale can cause slight damage in the local area, 4 moderate damage, 5 considerable damage, 6 severe damage
