demski, 57, flies a large american flag from a 132-foot flagpole outside his home day and night. but neighbors have been complaining they can't sleep because of the flapping noise
recent noise-meter measurements by city health officials found the flag exceeded legal limits for residential areas. they ordered demski to take his flag down every night at 10 p.m
