according to a korean official, both men laughed as chun suggested that after reagan leaves the white house early next year, they meet again to discuss life in retirement. reagan accepted, said the official, who asked not to be named
the two men also discussed the transition to democracy in south korea and the upcoming olympic games in seoul
reagan noted that korea's economic development was strengthened during chun's time in office and that his efforts contributed to the organization of the olympics, the official said
chun arrived here tuesday and will be leaving the united states on april 10. he will be traveling to new york, where he plans to meet with former president nixon and former secretary of state henry a. kissinger
