mohammed ali taskhiri addressed a conference of the 46-member organization of islamic conference, which has issued a statement about the palestinian rebellion but is is not expected to make headway toward a truce in the iran-iraq war. the persian gulf neighbors have been fighting since september 1980
taskhiri cited the revolution of ayatollah ruhollah khomeini against the pro-u.s. regime of the late shah mohammad reza pahlavi, which he called a ``nest of evil.'' the shah was ousted in february 1979
our children faced it like the children who are throwing stones in palestine, who are facing the enemy with his american weapons,'' taskhiri said
the zionist enemy is killing our children, is burning their bodies and breaking their arms and burying them alive,'' he said of the rebellion in the occupied west bank and gaza strip, which began dec. 8. more than 100 arabs have been killed
palestine is a moslem issue,'' he said. ``it is the main issue, but we haven't done anything about it yet except talk about it.''
