but the leftist guerrillas waging an 8-year-old war against the u.s.-backed government said tuesday the result of sunday's vote would make the nation ``ungovernable.'' a rebel commander said the electoral result _ an outright majority for the rightist opposition in the national legislature _ favors the guerrillas by giving the people ``a clear alternative.''
